733317f-a.folder: Lenox Avenue and 125th Street (West), Manhattan, N.Y.

715391f-b.title: Manhattan: 125th Street (West) - Lenox Avenue
715391f-b.text:
W. 125th Street, east fron Lenox Avenue. To the right
is the Marion Building, at the S.W. corner of this point. The
Harlem Branch of the Chatham Phenix National Bank is on the
north side of this thorouohfare and east of the Avenue. In the
far background is the Lee Building, located at the N.E. corner
of Park Averue and W. 125th Street. The automobiles in the fore-
ground obstruct a clear view of the N.Y.C.R.R. elevated tracks
and station at that point.
May 1928.
Geo. L. Balgue
The structures at the N.E. corner of Lenox Avenue and
W. 125th Street. Note at the right the bank building occupied
at this date by the ~anufacturers Trust Co.
July 28, 1932.
P.L. Sperr
